<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The recent run of bank failures in the US have=
 been smaller but less controlled than Credit Suisse, though still controll=
ed enough: Silicon Valley Bank, Signature Bank and Silvergate Bank were all=
 taken over by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corp. rather than being sold o=
ver a weekend to stronger banks like Credit Suisse was. Two possible reason=
s for that are:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Buying Credit Suisse at a slightly-abo=
ve-zero equity value was a good deal for UBS, while buying those banks at s=
lightly-above-zero equity values would=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>be good deals=
 for a buyer, so nobody wanted to buy them; or</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-b=
ottom: 5px;">Rescuing Credit Suisse was enough of a priority for Swiss regu=
lators that they were willing to combine their two largest banks into a sin=
gle far-too-big-to-fail national champion, but rescuing SVB was not enough =
of a priority for US regulators that they were willing to let, like, JPMorg=
an Chase &amp; Co. or Wells Fargo &amp; Co. buy it and get much bigger.</li=
>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Both of those things seem to have some truth t=
o them.=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30911=
506.258434/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvMzA4MGQzNjgtZDVhYS00MTI1LWEy=
MTAtNzE0ZTM3MDg3MDE3/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cD588f9f59" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Buying Cred=
it Suisse</a> =E2=80=9Ccould end up being a once-in-a-generation boon for U=
BS,=E2=80=9D while the US=E2=80=99s failed regional banks have uncertain fr=
anchises and enough interest-rate losses in their bond and loan portfolios =
that their assets might be worth less than their liabilities. But also Cred=
it Suisse=E2=80=99s regulators were single-mindedly focused on getting a de=
al done, while US regulators <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/30911506.258434/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGlj=
bGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMTYvc3ZiLWh1bnRzLWZvci1hLWJ1eWVyLWFmdGVyLXRlbnNlLWRyYWdnZWQ=
tb3V0LWZkaWMtc2FsZS1mYWlsZWQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMyMTIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZG=
l1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMzIxJnV0bV9jYW1wY=
Wlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfeb481ba" itemprop=3D"StoryLin=
k" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-=
decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color:=
 #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  intentiona=
lly discouraged too-big-to-fail banks</a> from bidding for SVB.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But you do have to sell them to someone eventu=
ally. Yesterday the FDIC sold most of Signature to New York Community Banco=
rp=E2=80=99s subsidiary Flagstar Bank NA. But=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30911506.258434/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZmRpYy5nb3=
YvbmV3cy9wcmVzcy1yZWxlYXNlcy8yMDIzL3ByMjMwMjEuaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
