 itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-de=
coration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #=
000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  this amazing=
 story</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The former owner of=C2=A0Silicon Valley Bank, =
seized earlier this month by regulators, asked a judge to force federal reg=
ulators to return as much as $2 billion the company says it needs to reorga=
nize in bankruptcy.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">SVB Financial Group=C2=A0was cut off from the =
money after the bank was taken over by regulators, who control the bank=E2=
=80=99s deposits, but not assets owned by SVB. The parent company has as mu=
ch as $2 billion in several accounts, including three at its former bank, w=
hich was renamed=C2=A0Bridge Bank=C2=A0after it was taken over. Regulators =
at the=C2=A0Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation=C2=A0have refused to give=
 SVB access to the accounts, according to court papers filed Sunday.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The dispute threatens to disrupt SVB=E2=80=99s=
 attempt to repay more than $3 billion the company owes bondholders. SVB fi=
led for bankruptcy last week in order to reorganize its non-bank assets and=
 repay creditors.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The FDIC has taken over Silicon Valley Bank an=
d is trying to sell it off, but it seems like it may not succeed in selling=
 the bank for more than it owes depositors, meaning that the FDIC =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0which has promised to pay all SVB depositors, including uninsured one=
s =E2=80=94=C2=A0might lose money on the deal.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile the holding company=E2=80=99s bondho=
lders, who are in some rough hypothetical sense junior to the depositors, s=
eem to be poised to get much of their money back, because the holding compa=
ny had assets other than the bank. One of those assets was $2 billion in ca=
sh. But that cash was held at SVB, and the FDIC, as a rather understandable=
 matter of rough justice, isn=E2=80=99t giving it back.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/30911506.258434/aHR0cHM6Ly9jbHNibHVlc2t5Lmxhdy5jb2x1=
bWJpYS5lZHUvMjAyMy8wMy8yMC9maW5hbmNpYWwtaW5zdGl0dXRpb24taW5ub3ZhdGlvbi1uZWV=
kZWQtaW4tc2lsaWNvbi12YWxsZXkv/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6355acd6" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 a proposal from Jeffrey Gordon</a> for =E2=80=9Cstorage=E2=80=9D bank acco=
unts at Silicon Valley Bank, in which holders would own stock in the bank a=
nd forfeit that stock if they redeemed their deposits early. Make the depos=
itors owners of the bank and maybe they won=E2=80=99t run on it.</p>
